                <h3>History of Squaw Creek</h3>
                <p>Squaw Creek Golf Course was built on land that was donated to the General Dynamics Recreation Association in 1969.</p>

                <p>Legendary course designer Ralph Plummer was hired to design the golf course with a total project cost of $1.1. million, including the clubhouse.</p>

                <p>In 2015 Colligan Golf Design was hired to do a major course renovation. Phase 1 was a state-of-the-art 14 acre practice facility complete with four short game practice greens and over 10,000 square feet of practice putting surface. The new driving range teeing area is more than triple its original size.</p>

                <p>In January of 2016 Colligan Golf Design began a major renovation of the course itself. Leaving the original layout intact, Colligan installed brand new USGA Mini Verde Bermuda greens, 419 Bermuda fairways and tees which include a new 4th set of tees that can shorten the course to 4800 yards.</p>

                <p>As Director of Golf, Lynn Vaughan, tells people when describing the renovation, “The layout is exactly the same…but every hole is different.”</p>

